info.name: Interoperability API
info.description:
This collection contains the syntax and examples of the 8 requests for the Interoperability API. The available requests are:

*   PassesPerStation
*   PassesAnalysis
*   PassesCost
*   ChargesBy
*   HealthCheck
*   ResetPasses
*   ResetStations
*   ResetVehicles
    

Also, apart from the path parameters for each request, there is a url parameter `format`, which can be set to `json` or `csv`, depending on the type of data that the user wants to receive.

request.description: This Request takes the parameters `stationID`, `date_from` and `date_to`. It returns all the recorded passes that happened at the requested station, in the specified time period.

This Request takes the parameters `op1_ID`, `op2_ID`, `date_from` and `date_to`. It returns all the recorded passes that happened at stations that belong to Operator with ID `op1_ID`, by vehicles whose Tag belongs to Operator with ID `op2_ID`.

This Request takes the parameters `op1_ID`, `op2_ID`, `date_from` and `date_to`. It returns the amount of passes that happened at stations that belong to Operator with ID `op1_ID`, by vehicles whose Tag belongs to Operator with ID `op2_ID`, along with their total cost.

This Request takes the parameters `op_ID`, `date_from` and `date_to`. For each Operator other than `op_ID`, it returns the number of passes and the total cost of all recorded passes that took place at stations that belong to Operator `op_ID`, by vehicles whose Tag was issued by the specific Operator.
Attempts to establish connection to the database, and returns the status.

response.name: HealthCheck

request.description: It attempts to erase all recorded passes from the database, and returns whether the deletion was successful or not.
It attempts to erase the station records in the database, and re-initialize the table with the sample data. It returns whether the reset was successful or not.
It attempts to erase the vehicle records in the database, and re-initialize the table with the sample data. It returns whether the reset was successful or not.
